page.title: 06HOUSING
page.content: The housing in this area is nothing special. I don't live in a terraced house, at least that's what people call the houses that are squashed up and packed like sardines.Walking down the street you could well be sick on the combinations of colours of some of the houses. For instance you may see a green one next to a bright pink one. The gardens of some houses look like the Amazon Jungle while others look like the front of Buckingham Palace. This is basically because some people don't bother to cut the grass while others want to give a good impression to outsiders. Our front garden can be classed as respectable which is not surprising because I always end up doing the gardening.
